St Vincent and the Grenadines has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).These include social distancing and no more than 30 customers allowed in the main supermarkets at any one time.
For information on how to return to the UK from St Vincent and the Grenadines, see Return to the UK
The St Vincent and the Grenadines Emergency Medical Service is asking the public to call the COVID-19 inquiries hotline on (+1 784) 534 4325 or e-mail coronavirustaskforcesvg@gmail.com if they suspect they might have contracted the virus, been exposed to it, or any other matters relating to the virus.
Entry and borders
All international flights have been suspended until further notice. The seaports of Bequia, Mustique, Canouan and Union Island have also been closed to yachts and pleasure craft.
A mandatory two-week self-quarantine period for anyone arriving in St Vincent and the Grenadines is being enforced. Quarantine of non-residents will be at the expense of the traveller.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
